{
  "texts": [
    "The first type includes abstracts that miss the main topic of the question (e.g.",
    "discuss heart failure instead of knee problems), which we considered completely irrelevant abstracts.",
    "The other type that discusses a more general topic and thus does not cover all the aspects of the question we considered partially irrelevant.",
    "This group could also be observed as the one that contains additional information but does not provide the direct answer to the question.",
    "It is crucial to recognize that there can be two types of mistakes when irrelevant abstracts are concerned."
  ]
}